CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 6, 1960, pg. A9 reads: "Frogs' Formal - The Frogs and their guests had a gay time dancing to the music of Walt Harper and his band which featured song stylist Dolores Ware. A partial view of the Gateway Plaza Ballroom is shown above, filled with dancers.  Miss Wares, left, belts out a song as Walt, himself, plays. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men and women dancing to Dolores Ware singing and Walt Harper playing piano in foreground, in Gateway Plaza for FROGS formal
